Mutual respect, peaceful co-existence, win-win cooperation are keys to bringing China-U.S. relations back on the right track, said Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi on Monday during the ongoing Two Sessions in Beijing. There is no winner in a trade war, and how China and the U.S. can find the right way forward and manage to get along is a formulation that must be worked out by the two countries together, as CGTN's Lily Lyu explains in this episode of BizBeat.